Name: datajs version 1.1.1
Description:
datajs is a cross-browser and UI agnostic JavaScript library that enables data-centric web applications with the following features:
* OData client that enables CRUD operations including batching and metadata support using both ATOM and JSON payloads.
* Single store abstraction that provides a common API on top of HTML5 local storage technologies.
* Data cache component that allows reading data ranges from a collection and storing them locally to reduce the number of network requests.

*Changes from DataJS 1.1.0 release*
* Support for Json minimalmetadata format with computation for Uris when metadata is provided, which reduces the payload size on the wire.
* Ability to read current version using datajs.version.
* Ability to parse XML metadata using OData.parseMetadata API.
* Bug fixes that include fixes for bugs 899, 980, 1049, 1110, 1111.
* Code cleanup.

Name: datajs version 1.0.3
Description:
datajs is a cross-browser and UI agnostic JavaScript library that enables data-centric web applications with the following features:

* OData client that enables CRUD operations including batching and metadata support using both ATOM and JSON payloads.
* Single store abstraction that provides a common API on top of HTML5 local storage technologies.
* Data cache component that allows reading data ranges from a collection and storing them locally to reduce the number of network requests.

+Changes from datajs 1.0.2+

The changes made since the previous release contain the following minor updates to support OData V3 services:

* The library will add the MaxDataServiceVersion header if missing from the request.
* The mime type for json payload has been changed to "application/json;odata=verbose"
* Minor fix for reading the responses to a batch request.
* Add the new EDM namespace to the metadata handler.

Despite these changes, the library still is an OData V2 client.

Name: datajs version 0.0.4
Description:
This release contains the following breaking changes:

* The data cache API destroy() has been renamed to clear(). 
* The data cache onprefetch event has been replaced by the onidle event that will fire whenever the cache is not performing any operations.
* The Indexed DB as a storage mechanism is no longer the mechanism of choice in Firefox 4 and it will be have to be requested explicitly when creating both cache and store objects. DOM storage is now considered the mechanism of choice in all browsers that support it.

Also this release adds to the library support for basic authentication by setting username and password in the requests. Support for configuring and controlling cache sizes as well as user defined cache data sources.  It also adds filtering forward/backwards to cache objects and support for using [url:RxJs|http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/devlabs/gg577609]. Finally, JSONP options can now be set on a per-request basis.

Name: datajs version 0.0.3
Description: This release adds a cache API that provides a very simple way of reading large paginated results, a store API that provides a common abstraction over a few mechanisms that can be used to store data locally and support for OData $links feeds.

Name: datajs version 0.0.2
Description: This release adds support for parsing DateTime and DateTimeOffset properties into javascript Date objects and serialize them back.

Name: datajs version 0.0.1
Description: This is an alpha release of a new project called ‘datajs’, a cross-browser JavaScript library that enables data-centric web applications by leveraging modern web protocols.
